<section id="cfp" class="twocol">
<div>
<h2>Call for Papers</h2>
<div class="card">
<p>We invite original, unpublished work on topics including zero-knowledge protocols and systems, post-quantum cryptography for decentralized networks, verifiable and privacy-preserving computation, decentralized identity (DID/VC), data availability and sampling, rollups and DA layers, MPC/threshold cryptography, CRDT-enabled P2P, and decentralized storage/compute markets.</p>
<p>Submissions should follow the host conference format and anonymization policy if applicable. Typical length: N pages excluding references; include an appendix for artifacts if needed.</p>
<p>At least one author of each accepted paper must register and present at the workshop.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<h2>News</h2>
<div class="card news">
<ul>
<li>[YYYY-MM-DD] Website launched.</li>
<li>[YYYY-MM-DD] CFP posted.</li>
<li>[YYYY-MM-DD] Submission site open.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h2 style="margin-top:16px">Artifacts</h2>
<div class="card">
<p>We welcome optional artifact evaluation. Links to code/data can be included as anonymized repositories during review.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>


